ZH: 我们周末常常去看戏。
EN: We often go to see performances on weekends.

ZH: 看戏对于我来说是一种放松。
EN: Watching performances is a form of relaxation for me.

ZH: 他们今晚在剧院看戏。
EN: They are watching a performance at the theater tonight.

ZH: 我们一起去看戏吧，好吗？
EN: Let's go watch a performance together, okay?

ZH: 我最喜欢在大剧院看戏了。
EN: I love watching performances in the grand theater the most.

ZH: 昨晚我在电视上看了一场好戏。
EN: Last night, I watched a good show on TV.

ZH: 每次过年，我们都会去看京剧表演。
EN: Every Chinese New Year, we always go watch Peking Opera performances.

ZH: 哥哥喜欢看武侠小说改编的戏。
EN: My brother likes to watch dramas adapted from martial arts novels.

ZH: 她喜欢去露天剧场看戏。
EN: She enjoys watching performances at the outdoor theater.

ZH: 明天我们要去看音乐剧。
EN: We are going to watch a musical tomorrow.

ZH: 老师鼓励我们一起参加学校的话剧表演。
EN: The teacher encouraged us to participate in the school's drama performance together.

ZH: 这是我第一次在剧院看外国戏剧。
EN: This is my first time watching a foreign drama at the theater.

ZH: 妈妈喜欢看喜剧，因为能让她忘记烦恼。
EN: My mom likes to watch comedies because they help her forget her worries.

ZH: 我真的很享受在家里看老电影。
EN: I really enjoy watching old movies at home.

ZH: 看了这出话剧，我对生命有了新的认识。
EN: After watching this play, I have a new understanding of life.

ZH: 弟弟正在看一个古代爱情故事的戏。
EN: My younger brother is watching a drama about an ancient love story.

ZH: 看这个连续剧真是让人上瘾。
EN: Watching this TV series is really addictive.

ZH: 小朋友们在学校操场上演了一出小品，我去看了戏。
EN: The children performed a sketch on the school playground, and I went to watch the show.

ZH: 他们每年都会去戏剧节上看戏。
EN: They go to the drama festival to watch performances every year.

ZH: 她在剧院看的戏让她热泪盈眶。
EN: The play she watched at the theater brought tears to her eyes.
